WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified computing profile for the Qualcomm Snapdragon 8 Elite Gen 5
mobile SoC. It defines the third-generation Oryon CPU core cluster, the
Adreno 840 GPU architecture, the Hexagon NPU AI inference pipeline, the
Spectra cognitive ISP (Image Signal Processor), and the LPDDR5x memory
subsystem. All parameters are expressed as formulas, not mere configuration.

WHY IT EXISTS
This SoC powers the 2026 generation of flagship Android devices including
the Samsung Galaxy S26 series. GIOP must model its computational resources
as auditable formulas to predict rendering latency, power consumption, and
AI inference throughput for any frame processed on-device.

HOW IT WORKS
CPU Performance Scaling (Amdahl's Law with Oryon v3):
  P(N) = 1 / ( (1 - f_parallel) + f_parallel / N )
  where f_parallel = 0.92 (measured across Geekbench 6.2 workloads),
  N = 8 cores. Two Prime cores at up to 4.74 GHz (single-thread critical
  path), six Performance cores at up to 3.63 GHz. The 8 MB shared L3 cache
  reduces off-chip memory access by 35% versus the previous generation.[reference:0]

CPU Dynamic Power (CMOS):
  P_cpu = C_eff * V^2 * f
  where C_eff ≈ 2.8 nF (per Prime core, 3 nm N3P TSMC), V = 0.65–1.05 V,
  f = 3.63–4.74 GHz. Sustained TDP: 6 W (smartphone passive cooling).

GPU Throughput (Adreno 840):
  TFLOPS_FP32 = (CUs * ALUs_per_CU * 2 * f_gpu) / 1e12
  = (6 * 128 * 2 * 1.3e9) / 1e12 ≈ 2.0 TFLOPS
  Ray tracing intersection rate = 2.4 Giga-rays/s (hardware BVH traversal).
  Rasterization throughput at 4K 120 Hz: pixel fill rate ≈ 32 Gpix/s.[reference:1]

NPU Inference Throughput (Hexagon):
  TOPS_INT8 = (MAC_units * 2 * f_npu) / 1e12
  ≈ (12,288 * 2 * 2.0e9) / 1e12 ≈ 49 TOPS
  AI efficiency improved by 37% generationally via sparse convolution
  skipping and INT4 precision support.[reference:2]

ISP Throughput (Spectra Cognitive):
  Pixel_rate = f_isp * pixels_per_cycle
  = 1.5e9 * 16 ≈ 24 Gpix/s
  Supports 320 MP single-shot capture, 8K 60 fps HDR video encode
  (HEVC/AV1), real-time semantic segmentation up to 12 layers at 4K.

Memory Bandwidth (LPDDR5x-5300):
  BW = bus_width_bytes * f_data * 2 (DDR)
  = 8 * 5.3e9 * 2 = 84.8 GB/s[reference:3]

